canonical:
  title: 朴杏山全之宅有題
  author: 洪奎
  language: lzh
  text: 酒盞常須滿茶甌不用深杏山終日雨細細更論心
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 朴杏山全之宅有題
  author: 洪奎
  language: lzh
  text: 酒盞常須滿。茶甌不用深。杏山終日雨。細細更論心。
korean:
  title: 박행산 전지 댁에 제하며
  author: 홍규
  language: kor
  text: |-
    술잔은 모름지기 항상 가득해야 하느니
    차 그릇은 반드시 가득 부을 필요가 없는 것일세
    행산에 하루 종일 비가 오는데
    다시 세세히 마음을 논하네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0220_010_0320&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Written at Park Haengsan's Cottage
  author: Hong Gyui
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Wine cups must always brim full,
    Yet tea bowls need not overflow—
    All day the rain falls on Apricot Mountain,
    And in its gentle persistence, the heart finds discourse.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: Apricot Mountain (杏山) refers to Park Haengsan's residence, playing on the character for 'apricot' (杏) in his name.
  - key: ''
    value: The poem contrasts the fullness required for wine with the restraint appropriate for tea, suggesting different approaches to life's pleasures and contemplation.
